# Apollo Linux default user skeleton
# Copied to each new user's home at account creation

# ~/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini  →  installed by apollo-themes
# ~/.config/openbox/               →  symlinked from /usr/share/apollo/openbox
# ~/.config/picom/                 →  copied from /usr/share/apollo/picom
# ~/.config/dunst/                 →  copied from /usr/share/apollo/dunst
# ~/.config/alacritty/             →  copied from /usr/share/apollo/alacritty
# ~/.config/hypr/                  →  copied from /usr/share/apollo/hyprland (if Hyprland mode)

# This file is intentionally minimal.
# The actual skel directory is assembled during:
#  1. ISO build (build.sh copies /usr/share/apollo/* configs)
#  2. Calamares (apollo-desktop-select.py copies to /etc/skel in target)
#  3. User creation (adduser copies /etc/skel to ~/)
#
# Result: every new user gets Apollo Desktop configured out-of-the-box.
